    <mxCell id="wbody" value="Teams design what they believe is a clean passed-state handoff. Then they add a 'global context' object that all agents read and write without defined authority rules. The global context becomes the shared state problem the handoff abstraction was supposed to eliminate. Every production multi-agent system has one. Finding it — and defining explicit write authority rules for every field — is non-negotiable work before go-live." style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#7A6000;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
